        "generatedLyrics": "[Intro]\n\n[Verse]\nDusty dashboard, windows down low\nRadio hummin' a song we know\nGot my best friend, fur soft and deep\nWhile the miles and memories sleep\nHe's got his paws up on the glass\nWatchin' the green world flyin' past\n\n[Pre-Chorus]\nEvery town a blur, a fleeting dream\nChasin' the sunbeams, it would seem\nHe purrs a rhythm, soft and true\nEverything feels brand new\n\n[Chorus]\nOh, sun-kissed whiskers, on the breeze\nThrough the fields and shady trees\nThis old car, a rolling home\nWith my feline, never alone\nSummer haze and open road\nLightenin' up my heavy load\n\n[Post-Chorus]\nYeah, never alone\nWith my feline, never alone\n\n[Break]\n\n[Verse]\nStopping for gas, he takes a peek\nA tiny yawn, a silent squeak\nHe likes the sunshine on his face\nFinds his own quiet little space\nWe share a snack, a gentle pat\nJust me and my adventurous cat\n\n[Pre-Chorus]\nEvery town a blur, a fleeting dream\nChasin' the sunbeams, it would seem\nHe purrs a rhythm, soft and true\nEverything feels brand new\n\n[Chorus]\nOh, sun-kissed whiskers, on the breeze\nThrough the fields and shady trees\nThis old car, a rolling home\nWith my feline, never alone\nSummer haze and open road\nLightenin' up my heavy load\n\n[Bridge]\nRemember that diner, late at night?\nHe slept right through, a peaceful sight\nUnder the glow of neon signs\nLost in his own feline designs\nThis simple joy, it fills my soul\nMakes this journey feel so whole\n\n[Verse]\nWe're heading west, no map in hand\nJust feelin' the pull of distant land\nHe stretches out, a lazy grace\nContentment on his furry face\nAnother sunset paints the sky\nAs another mile goes rolling by\n\n[Chorus]\nOh, sun-kissed whiskers, on the breeze\nThrough the fields and shady trees\nThis old car, a rolling home\nWith my feline, never alone\nSummer haze and open road\nLightenin' up my heavy load\n\n[Post-Chorus]\nYeah, never alone\nWith my feline, never alone\n\n[Outro]",
